QUICK START (Lab PC)
--------------------
1. Plug in USB stick
2. Double-click START_DEMO.bat
3. Wait ~60 seconds for models to load
4. Browser opens automatically at http://localhost:5000
5. Green dot in top-left = all 3 models ready

WHAT THE DEMO SHOWS
--------------------
ZPhisher is a real-time social engineering detection system
that classifies blockchain communications using THREE models:

  - TF-IDF + Logistic Regression (baseline)
  - DistilBERT fine-tuned on general email data
  - DistilBERT domain-adapted on blockchain communications

The live feed streams pre-loaded blockchain messages through
all three models simultaneously, showing confidence scores
and model agreement/disagreement in real time.

The manual input box accepts any text and classifies it
through all three models instantly (Ctrl+Enter to submit).

HINT PILLS
----------
Click the coloured pills above the input box to load
pre-written examples covering different attack types:
  - Fake airdrop        - Seed phrase scam
  - Founder impersonation  - Legitimate transaction
  - Legitimate staking  - Borderline HR scam

KEY FINDINGS TO DISCUSS
------------------------
General F1 (email test set):
  TF-IDF baseline:     0.9789
  DistilBERT general:  0.9900

Blockchain F1 (blockchain eval set):
  TF-IDF baseline:     0.6757  <- domain gap
  DistilBERT general:  0.6667  <- domain gap
  DistilBERT adapted:  1.0000  <- domain adaptation works

The domain gap (0.99 -> 0.67) is the central research finding.
The adapted model (1.0) demonstrates this gap is addressable.

FOLDER STRUCTURE
----------------
ZPhisher/
├── START_DEMO.bat           <- run this to start
├── app.py                   <- Flask backend (3 models)
├── demo.html                <- dashboard frontend
├── model_checkpoint/        <- general DistilBERT weights
├── model_checkpoint_adapted/ <- blockchain-adapted weights
├── data/
│   └── processed/
│       └── train.csv        <- training data for TF-IDF
├── server.log               <- created at runtime (ignore)
└── README.txt               <- this file

REQUIREMENTS
------------
- Windows 10/11 (64-bit)
- Python 3.9+ installed (lab PCs should have this)
- Internet connection (first run only, to install packages)
- ~4GB free RAM
- Modern browser (Chrome/Edge/Firefox)

If Python is not installed on the lab PC, contact your
supervisor in advance to arrange a suitable machine.

STOPPING THE DEMO
-----------------
Press any key in the black terminal window to stop the
server cleanly when your inspection is complete.

TROUBLESHOOTING
---------------
- Browser shows "Cannot reach server": wait 30 more seconds
  for models to load, then refresh
- Red dot in header: models still loading, wait
- Green dot but feed not starting: click Resume Feed button
- Port 5000 already in use: restart the batch file

